<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup: Eb I, gentle two-note RH opener, Eb2-Bb2-Eb3 LH open 5th.
- Bar 1: Four chords (V-I-vi-V) with full 4-note LH. Non-diatonic C major → Cm(vi).
- Bar 2: Eb sustained dotted half, cadential Bb — Eb I triad RH.
- Bar 3: vi-I-vii°-I pattern. Non-diatonic G#° → Ddim (vii°), D2-Ab2-D3-F3 in LH.
- Bar 4: Bb7 with 7th color (F4-Ab4-C5 in RH) for richness before phrase 2.
- Bar 5: Descending melody Eb5-D5-C5-Bb4 against climbing LH inner voices.
- Bar 6: Non-diatonic F major → Fm(ii). Fm provides subdominant color (Ab in bass).
- Bar 7: Cm7 in beat 3 — LH uses C2-G2-Bb2-Eb3 spread (m7 intervals).
- Bar 8: Final Eb I with full 4-note LH, ending on dotted-half before rest.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 1 RH: G4-G4-G4-F4 sustained inner voice, stepwise descent to Bb beat 4.
- Bar 3 Ddim: F4-Ab4 in RH, D2-Ab2 tritone in bass — authentic vii° color.
- Bar 5 LH descent: Eb2-Bb2→Bb2-F3→C2-G2→G2-D3 — each bass moves by 4th/5th.
- Bar 7 Cm7: LH C2-G2-Bb2-Eb3 — stacked 5th+3rd+4th, avoids parallel 5ths.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup: single chord entry, minimal
- mm. 1-4: Phrase 1 establishes Eb with regular chord rhythm, grows to Bb7
- mm. 5-8: Phrase 2 fuller texture — all 4 beats harmonized, climax at bar 5, final resolution
-->
